<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 3:26AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Catoosa, western
Murray, Floyd, Whitfield, southeastern Walker, western Gordon,
northern Polk, central Chattooga and western Bartow Counties through
400 AM EDT...
At 326 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from East Brainerd to Etna, and moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rome, Dalton, Calhoun, Cedartown, Lafayette, Summerville, Chatsworth,
Ringgold, Fort Oglethorpe, Adairsville, Rockmart, Trion, Varnell,
Aragon, Cave Spring, Tunnel Hill, Cohutta, Kingston, Resaca and
Plainville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 AM EDT for northwestern
Georgia.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM EDT for
northwestern Georgia.</instruction>
